      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="365-06E2"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">Written in the year 1724.&#13;</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"></l></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"></l></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">D</hi>Ear Sir, I think 'tis doubly hard,</l><l/><l n="2" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-2">Your ears and doors should both be barr'd.</l><l/><l n="3" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-3">Can any thing be more unkind?</l><l/><l n="4" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-4">Must I not see, 'cause you are blind?</l><l/><l n="5" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-5">Methinks, a friend at night should cheer you,</l><l/><l n="6" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-6">A friend that loves to see and hear you.</l><l/><l n="7" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-7">Why am I robb'd of that delight,</l><l/><l n="8" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-8">When you can be no loser by't?</l><l/><l n="9" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-9">Nay, when 'tis plain (for what is plainer?)</l><l/><l n="10" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-10">That if you heard, you'd be no gainer.</l><l/><l n="11" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-11">For sure you are not yet to learn,</l><l/><l n="12" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-12">That hearing is not your concern;</l><l/><l n="13" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-13">Then be your doors no longer barr'd:</l><l/><l n="14" xml:id="spp-365-06E2-line-14">Your business, Sir, is to be heard.</l><l/><l/></lg></div>
      </div>
